I love the "peek" capability in vscode.  But I would like to see it's use expanded to allow peeking to files referenced by the current file.

For example take this angular 2 component:

```
@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  templateUrl: './heros.tmpl.html',
  styleUrls: ['heros.tmpl.css'],
}
export class AppComponent {
 ...
}
```

I think it would be sweet if I could put my cursor on top of the './heros.tmpl.html' string and select to "peek" to that file and show it inline so I can edit it along with the code file. 

Would it be possible to add this?  Does the current API allow this type of thing to be added using the extension API?  (if someone gives me a basic idea of how to add it I would be willing to give it a try)

